data.title: Drake f/ Lil Durk - "Laugh Now Cry Later"
data.text:
Post by jdanton2 on

if Ariana or Bruno is on it i would be alright with this release .

Post by Nick on

if Ariana or Bruno is on it i would be alright with this release .

I thought it was confirmed that Bruno is on the first single.

Post by Deleted on

I hope Bruno will take Drake straight from Mars back to Earth and grass level, if not smokin it, this might be the end of A-virus.

Post by Deleted on

I'm not sure if he will cry later, but not gonna be happy seeing this dull thing flopping hard.

Post by leonagwen on

Everything this guy releases sounds the same. I think people are finally getting sick of him. His days of having #1 hits are probably over. He will still get top 20 hits because of his name.

Post by Deleted on

For what it is, it's a nice song. And it will be interesting to hear Lil Durk on pop radio. But yes, Drake is on cruise control. Years of success appeared to have drained him of any desire to innovate. It'll probably perform a bit worse than Toosie Slide.

Post by Choco on

Again? I swear I've heard him do this song before, and better.

Post by kcdawg13 on

I like the song a lot, I find it to be very uplifting. However it does feel like Drake was attempting to remake God's Plan.

Post by Enigma. on

Everything this guy releases sounds the same. I think people are finally getting sick of him. His days of having #1 hits are probably over. He will still get top 20 hits because of his name.

He just had one earlier this year and has one of the biggest hits of 2020 with Future.

I mean I am not even fan of his these days but definitely wouldn't go THAT far.

Post by g8erboi on

I mean... it’s better than Toosie Slide, but that’s not saying much.

Post by Deleted on

He has made this hit a few times, but every time it was successful, so I can't blame him.

Never thought I'd see the day where a Cardi B song would block a Drake lead single from #1 on Spotify and likely the Hot 100.

Forgot to say I like this. Happy that Durk gets some more mainstream love.
